10/9/01
  Overnight test: NETDELAY=200, ADDELAY=800 => works fine.
    No Digitran drop out.

  Add code to print SMPTE to study cue tone forward accuracy problem.

  PPC noticed that some time PTS offset return offset2 of 0.
  It is because at that time the network channel has just been initialized
  due to the return switch request.  Should not reset time base offsets
  to handle this case.


